CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 13, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost...Sometimes Home is Where the Heart Remains - Where the Hamiltons Lived - Next door at 19 Watt Street was the home of the family of Hamiltons, left to two daughters and a son. Only the foundations of the house and rubble are left today."
TitMainTitle: Overgrown vacant lot with debris and tree with area of striped bark, 19 Watt Street, Hill District
